 ------
 Maven 2 JavaNCSS Plugin
 ------

Maven 2 JavaNCSS Plugin

  JavaNCSS plugin which generates code metric analysis.

*Available Configuration Options
 
*-------------------------+--------------*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
 <<Parameter>>            | <<Optional>> | <<Description>>                                                                                     
*-------------------------+----------*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
 lineThreshold            | Yes      | Number of lines to keep for objects & functions report. Default to 30.
*-------------------------+----------*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
 tempFileName             | Yes      | Temporary filename for raw xml output from JavaNcss. Default to javancss-raw-report.xml
*-------------------------+----------*---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+ 

*How to Generate JavaNCSS Report

  In your project pom.xml, add the javaNcss plugin in <reporting> section.

-------------------
  <project>
      ...
      <reporting>
          <plugins>
              <plugin>
                  <groupId>org.codehaus.mojo</groupId>
                  <artifactId>javancss-maven-plugin</artifactId>
                  <version>2.0-alpha1-SNAPSHOT</version>
              </plugin>
          </plugins>
      </reporting>
      ...
  </project>
-------------------    

  Execute the site plugin to generate the report distribution.

-------------------
  mvn site:site
-------------------  